  In a natural market environment, the price prediction model needs to be
updated in real time according to the data obtained by the system to ensure the
accuracy of the prediction. In order to improve the user experience of the
system, the price prediction function needs to use the fastest training model
and the model prediction fitting effect of the best network as a predictive
model. We conduct research on the fundamental theories of RNN, LSTM, and BP
neural networks, analyse their respective characteristics, and discuss their
advantages and disadvantages to provide a reference for the selection of
price-prediction models.
